The paper discusses Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks and proposes a new DDoS mitigation solution that leverages Named Data Networking (NDN) architecture. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses security issues related to DDoS attacks, which could also place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. The paper also discusses the impact of DDoS attacks on service providers, which could place it in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The paper also discusses the Internet of Things (IoT), which could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. Finally, the paper proposes a new solution for DDoS mitigation, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) category.
